                    <p class="title">Depreciation Pass-Through and Cost Segregation</p>
                    <p>With current IRS rules, owners and investors in commercial multifamily properties can depreciate
                        the value of an asset every year, typically through a process called cost segregation. This
                        process reduces both the property’s taxable income and tax liability. This incentive for
                        owner/investors to maximize the depreciation amount each year provides unique tax benefits not
                        available with most asset classes. As with any investment decision you make, you should consult
                        with a certified/licensed tax advisor to evaluate your specific needs.</p></div>
